Sticktion (stik-shon) Is a widely accepted technical term for machinery or instrumation that sticks before moving. Instruments like Pressure or level gauges that either jump up the scale suddenly where there is not matching pressure surge, or if something needs a dunt to get it moving. Likewise machinery that seems to stck then suddenly move again, is said to be down to a bit of "sticktion", which is probably the true result of the sum or the friction of all the moving parts.